---
title: Tex-Mex Beef Lettuce Wraps with Pickled Shallot & Tortilla Chips
description: For a lighter spin on loaded beef burritos, we turn to crisp, refreshing baby lettuce leaves. Load up those leaves with Tex-Mex-spiced ground beef sizzled to perfection in a hot pan, then top with pickled shallot, sour cream, and crunchy tortilla chips for the perfect balance of hearty flavor and crisp, crunchy texture—all in 20 minutes!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6765a54e9bfc6de73c8e1d53-20639a21.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6765a54e9bfc6de73c8e1d53-en-US.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 570 kcal
  fat: 39 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 24 g
  sugar: 6 g
  protein: 28 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 720 mg
time required: 20 minutes
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/tex-mex-beef-lettuce-wraps-6765a54e9bfc6de73c8e1d53
cuisine: North America
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Trim and
discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}(trimmed); separate leaves. Reserve 6 whole
leaves (12 whole leaves for 4 servings); thinly slice remaining lettuce.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine shallot, @white wine vinegar{5%tsp},
@white sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and
microwave until shallot is bright pink, ~{30-60%seconds}. Set aside to pickle,
stirring occasionally.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add @ground beef{10%oz}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until cooked
through, ~{4-6%minutes} (if there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it
out).

Stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1} and @water{1/4%cup}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
beef is evenly coated and sauce is warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Taste and
season with @salt and @pepper if desired.

> Ground beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Gently crush @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%oz} in their #bag{}.

Divide lettuce leaves between plates. Fill with sliced lettuce, Tex-Mex beef, and
as much pickled shallot as you like (draining first). Drizzle with
@sour cream{1.5%tbsp} (cut a corner of the pouch to make a piping bag!) and
sprinkle with crushed tortilla chips. Serve.

> For the pickled shallot: use 1/2 tsp sugar for 4 servings.